                <Header>Abandoned Mine Land Inventory System</Header>
                <Paragraph>To provide information for implementing the Surface Mining Control and Reclamation Act of 1977, the OSMRE maintains an inventory of land and water affected by past mining. The inventory contains information on the location, type, and extent of abandoned mine land impacts, as well as information on the reclamation costs. The inventory is based on field surveys by State, tribal, and OSMRE program officials.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
